Task
Formatting array elements
You need to format the elements of the array:
• element with index 0 - up to 0 decimal places;
• element with index 1 - up to 1 decimal places;
• element with index 2 - up to 2 decimal places;
• element with index 3 - up to 3 decimal places; and so on.
Write a function named formatArray that takes an array arr as an argument and returns an array in which each element is formatted according to the given rule.
Example:
• function formatArray ([1.345, 2.234, 3.1234, 4.56789]) should return [1, 2.2, 3.12, 4.568].

Solution
function formatArray (arr) {
 for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
  arr [i] = (arr [i]). toFixed (i);
  }
return arr.map (Number);
}
